pisode|accessdate=May 23, 2014|newspaper=Herald-Dispatch (Huntington, WV)|date=October 29, 2008}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2009, Rahall jumped out of a plane to show his support for the coal industry. The event was intended to show the importance of the coal industry to both West Virginia and the United States as a whole. The act confused some, who questioned the reasoning behind the jump. It was noted that Rahall is involved with coal lobbyists and also receives contributions from the airline industry.<ref name=\"Plane for Coal\">{{cite news|title=Nick Rahall Jumps From a Plane for Coal. Here\u2019s Why.|url=http://washingtonindependent.com/51792/nick-rahall-jumps-from-a-plane-for-coal-heres-why|newspaper=Washington Independent|date=July 20, 2009}}</ref><ref name=\"Coal Lobby\">{{cite news|title=Rep. Nick Rahall Jumps Out Of A Plane For The Coal Lobby|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2009/07/20/rep-nick-rahall-jumps-out_n_241419.html|newspaper=The Huffington Post|date=August 20, 2009|first=Katherine|last=Goldstein}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.house.gov/rahall/ Congressman Nick Rahall] official U.S. House site\n*[http://www.nickrahall.com/ Congressman Nick Rahall]\n*{{Dmoz|Regional/North_America/United_States/West_Virginia/Government/Federal/US_House_of_Representatives/Nick_Rahall_%5BD-3%5D}}\n*{{CongLinks | congbio = r000011 | ballot = Nick_Rahall | nndb = 252/000040132 | votesmart = 27133 | govtrack = 400331 | opencong = 400331 | rollcall = 536 | politifact = | fec = H6WV04057 | opensecrets = N00002198 | assets = nick-rahall | legistorm = 434/Rep_Nick_Joe_Rahall_II.html | followthemoney = | ontheissues = House/Nick_Rahall.htm | congress = nick-rahall/940 | worldcat = np-rahall,%20nick | cspan = 8272 | imdb = 3003478 | bloomberg = | nyt = | washpo = gIQAtE0HAP }}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|us-hs}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Ken Hechler]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Member of the [[List of United States Representatives from West Virginia|U.S. Ho